# Vendored: luacheck (pure-Lua subset)

## Origin

Upstream repository: https://github.com/lunarmodules/luacheck
Pinned commit:       f47ad699b5aab8eba5494a2b63e26c24dbf486ce
Branch:              master (as of 2026-06-07)
Upstream version:    1.2.0 (luacheck._VERSION in init.lua)
License:             MIT (see LICENSE below)

## Subset manifest

This directory contains ONLY the pure-Lua module tree reachable from
`luacheck.check_strings` and `luacheck.get_report`. Files that depend on
`luafilesystem` (lfs), CLI infrastructure, the config-file loader, the
caching layer, the rockspec expander, or the profiler have been excluded.

### Included (38 files)

Core path (luacheck/):
  init.lua              — luacheck public API: check_strings, get_report,
                          process_reports, get_message
  check.lua             — per-source check driver (calls stages pipeline)
  check_state.lua       — mutable state threaded through stages
  core_utils.lua        — sort_by_location and shared helpers
  decoder.lua           — UTF-8 / encoding helpers used by lexer
  filter.lua            — apply options to raw reports
  format.lua            — get_message (issue → human text)
  lexer.lua             — Lua lexer
  options.lua           — option validation / merging
  parser.lua            — Lua parser (produces AST)
  standards.lua         — globals-table and std-table validation
  unicode.lua           — unicode classification
  unicode_printability_boundaries.lua — printability boundary tables
  utils.lua             — shared utilities (array helpers, try/catch wrapper,
                          etc.; io/lfs functions present but unreachable via
                          check_strings — see analysis in docs/internals/lint.md)

Stages (luacheck/stages/):
  init.lua              — stage registry and pipeline runner
  parse.lua             — AST entry point
  unwrap_parens.lua     — parenthesis-unwrap pass
  linearize.lua         — control-flow linearization
  parse_inline_options.lua — inline --luacheck: comment parsing
  name_functions.lua    — function-name inference
  resolve_locals.lua    — local-variable scope resolution
  detect_bad_whitespace.lua
  detect_compound_operators.lua
  detect_cyclomatic_complexity.lua
  detect_empty_blocks.lua
  detect_empty_statements.lua
  detect_globals.lua    — undefined/unused globals (W1xx codes)
  detect_reversed_fornum_loops.lua
  detect_unbalanced_assignments.lua
  detect_uninit_accesses.lua
  detect_unreachable_code.lua
  detect_unused_fields.lua
  detect_unused_locals.lua  — unused locals (W2xx codes)

Builtin standards (luacheck/builtin_standards/):
  init.lua              — built-in globals catalog (lua51…lua54, love, ngx…)
  love.lua, luanti.lua, ngx.lua, playdate.lua  — framework std tables

### Excluded (lfs / CLI / file I/O / threading)

  fs.lua                — requires luafilesystem
  cache.lua             — file-based cache (requires fs)
  config.lua            — config-file loader (requires fs, cache, globbing)
  expand_rockspec.lua   — rockspec reader (requires fs)
  globbing.lua          — glob expansion (requires fs)
  main.lua              — CLI entry point (requires config, runner, version)
  runner.lua            — multi-file runner (requires fs, config, cache)
  version.lua           — version reporter (requires lfs, argparse, lanes)
  multithreading.lua    — LuaLanes threading (not applicable in-engine)
  serializer.lua        — binary serializer for cache (not needed)
  profiler.lua          — performance profiler
  vendor/sha1/          — used only by cache.lua and profiler.lua

## Upgrade policy

To upgrade: pin a new commit, re-run the subset copy, update this NOTICE,
re-run the spike test. Do not add lfs-dependent files to the subset.

